The paper deals with pairwise comparisons, which are often used in decision making, and proposes a new measure of inconsistency. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Decision Support Systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses inconsistency indices, which are related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper provides numerical comparisons, which could be related to Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
